@defvr {Constant} zeroa
@code{zeroa} represents an infinitesimal above zero. @code{zeroa} can be used in
expressions. @code{limit} simplifies expressions which contain infinitesimals.

See also @code{zerob} and @code{limit}.

Example:

@code{limit} simplifies expressions which contain infinitesimals:

@c ===beg===
@c limit(zeroa);
@c limit(zeroa+x);
@c ===end===
@example
(%i1) limit(zeroa);
(%o1)                                  0
(%i2) limit(x+zeroa);
(%o2)                                  x
@end example

@opencatbox
@category{Constants}
@closecatbox
@end defvr

